Despite the fact that the opening of the North - the northern territory on the 49th parallel - the Prime Minister has recently often mentioned in his statements, so far it has never been the subject of a presentation.
The prime minister, however, limited himself to explaining why the North represents a "jewel with enormous potential", but did not give a deadline, the amount of investment, or a clear priority in future projects.
